The molecular functional group structure of the prepared photocatalysts was demonstrated by FT-IR spectra (Fig. 5
                        ). The stretching vibration of O-H in adsorption water and bound water resulted in the strong peaks at 3300 cm−1 and 1637 cm−1 respectively [33]. In all Ag3PO4-based photocatalysts, the peaks at 558 cm−1 and 1010 cm−1 originated from the stretching vibration of P-O in phosphate, and the peak at 1383 cm−1 was due to the stretching vibration of P = O [34]. In all BiVO4-containing photocatalysts, the strong peak at 735 cm−1 was due to the ν3 antisymmetric stretching vibration mode of the VO4 
                        [35]. It can be seen from the spectra that Y3+-doping photocatalyst did not change the molecular structure of Ag3PO4, which concurred with the result of XRD. The observed characteristic peaks of Y-Ag3PO4 and BiVO4 in Y-Ag3PO4/CQDs/BiVO4 demonstrated that Y-Ag3PO4, CQDs and BiVO4 were combined in the ternary photocatalyst.
